Fifty-three people are killed in a 72-hour period in Ciudad Juarez, Mexico. (CNN)The United States Senate defeated a measure that would have banned the Environmental Protection Agency from regulating greenhouse gas emissions under the Clean Air Act (United States). The new regulations which began being applied early this year affect air polluters such as power plants and oil refineries, attempts to address climate change mitigation. (Reuters) (New York Times)Washington Times(Bloomberg)